File: The Hawks arrested the four on Thursday morning for alleged tender irregularities. JOHANNESBURG - Four former senior Gauteng Department of Health officials will appear in court on fraud, corruption and money laundering charges. It relates to IT tender fraud to the value of R1.2-billion. The Hawks arrested the four on Thursday morning for alleged tender irregularities. The investigation dates back to February 2007. It's alleged the four were part of a group involved in an IT maintenance programme at the department. READ: Businesswoman granted bail, facing fraud charges The total cost of such a project was meant to be no more than R57-million over three-years. The contract was instead awarded to a private entity at a cost of around R1.2-billion. Two private company directors will also be charged. They have not yet been arrested as they are out of the country